First Lady Rachael Ruto on Sunday attended the 27th Ordinary General Assembly of the Organization of African First Ladies for Development (OAFLAD) in Addis Ababa. During the assembly, the First Lady delivered the remarks of the First Lady of The United States Of America Jill Biden. This year's theme, "Closing Gaps in Gender Equity," was extensively discussed. Leaders who attended were the OAFLAD secretariat, First Ladies, technical advisors, high-level government officials, African Union, and development partners. Mama Rachael shared her interventions in promoting women's economic empowerment, climate action, and faith diplomacy in Kenya. She emphasised on the need for continued collaboration and collective action with all stakeholders, particularly in strengthening women's role in economic development and mitigating the effects of climate change.